songs.title: Grown
songs.lyrics:
[Intro: Jess Glynne]
[Humming]

[Verse 1: Perrie Edwards with Jesy Nelson & Leigh-Anne Pinnock]
Hold up, wait, you used to be a frenemy
Back then, boy, you didn't even notice me
Why now, you tryna get a hold of me?
We never even spoke so what makes you think you know me?
It's funny how the tables turn
I'm sitting back, baby, watching you burn
No regrets, it's a lesson learned
'Cause what you think ain't my concern

[Pre-Chorus: Jesy Nelson & Jade Thirlwall + Jesy Nelson]
About time that I let you know
My ride and I assume control
You blew it, baby, years ago
Can't get with me, now I'm grown (Hey)

[Chorus: All & Jade Thirlwall + Jesy Nelson]
Grown now, grown now
Don't you know that I'm grown now, grown now?
Don't you know that I can hold my own?
Boy, you missed the boat
Can't get with me, now I'm grown (Hey)

[Verse 2: Jesy Nelson & Jade Thirlwall]
Your voice dropped, you thought that you could handle me
You claimed me but now you trying to holla me
You're washed up and now I'm in a different league
You're trying way too hard and I don't need your flattery
Now, it's funny how the tables turn
I'm sitting back, baby, watching you burn
No regrets it's a lesson learned
'Cause what you think ain’t my concern

[Pre-Chorus: Jesy Nelson, Perrie Edwards & Jade Thirlwall + Jesy Nelson]
About time that I let you know (I let you know)
My ride and I assume control (Oh-oh-ohh)
You blew it, baby, years ago
Can't get with me, now I'm grown (Hey)

[Chorus: All & Jade Thirlwall + Jesy Nelson]
Grown now, grown now
Don't you know that I'm grown now, grown now?
Don't you know that I can hold my own?
Boy, you missed the boat
Can't get with me, now I'm grown (Hey)

[Bridge: Jesy Nelson with Leigh-Anne Pinnock, Perrie Edwards & Jade Thirlwall]
Hey, you didn't want me it took too long (You didn't want me) (Me-e)
You didn't want me and now I'm grown (You didn't want me) (Me-e) (Yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah)
Oh, what a shame, baby, now I'm grown (Oh, woah, eh-yeah, yeah-eh-yeah)

[Chorus: All, Leigh-Anne Pinnock, Jesy Nelson & (Jade Thirlwall)]
Grown now, grown now
Don't you know that I'm grown now, grown now? (I'm grown)
Don't you know that I can hold my own? (Oh, woah)
Boy, you missed the boat
(Can't get with me, now I'm grown) (Yeah, eh-eh)
Grown now, grown now
Don't you know that I'm grown now, grown now? (Woah, ooh, ooh)
Don't you know that I can hold my own?
Boy, you missed the boat
(Can't get with me, now I'm grown)
